<%#
  Limitations & confidence section for the claim PDF (ADR-018).

  Provenance-derived, factual voice (not apologetic boilerplate). Uses the
  measurement's confidence value and source to generate a concrete statement.

  Locals:
    measurement   Measurement
%>
<% ctx = report_limitations_context(measurement) %>
<div class="report-limitations print-only">
  <h3 class="report-section-heading">Limitations &amp; Confidence</h3>
  <p class="report-limitations-text">
    <% if ctx.confidence_pct %>
      Overall measurement confidence: <%= ctx.confidence_pct %>%.
    <% end %>
    <% if ctx.has_lidar %>
      Measurements derived from public LiDAR (USGS 3DEP) and satellite imagery;
      geometry computed by RANSAC plane fitting on building-classified points.
    <% else %>
      Measurements derived from satellite imagery; LiDAR coverage was not
      available for this location, so a planimetric estimation was used.
    <% end %>
    Pitch values are derived from the point cloud; field verification is
    recommended for roofing-permit submissions. Roof-mounted features (vents,
    skylights) are detected by vision model and may require manual confirmation.
    This report is generated from publicly available data and does not constitute
    a licensed engineering survey.
  </p>
</div>
